Privacy Policy
Last modified 30 January 2023

Accepting the Terms
By accessing and using any UBC application you agree to this Privacy policy

Information We Collect
We do not collect any personal data or share personal data with any third-party advertisers or ad networks for their advertising purposes.

Sensitive Data
By downloading and using any application from UBC, we do not assume that you are of any particular religious denomination or are expressing to us any particular religious belief; we merely assume that you are interested in our applications. We do not require that users provide such beliefs to us or provide any other sensitive data such as race, ethnicity, philosophical beliefs, or physical or mental health.

Third-party Information Collection
This Privacy Policy applies only to sites and applications that are owned and operated by UBCZ. Please keep in mind that UBC applications may contain links to other websites or apps. You are responsible for reviewing the privacy statements and policies of those other websites you choose to link to or from our apps, so that you can understand how those websites collect, use and store your information. We are not responsible for the privacy statements, policies or content of other websites or apps, including websites you link to or from UBC applications. Websites containing co-branding (referencing our name and a third party’s name) containing content delivered by the third party and not us.

Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices. We will post any changes to our Privacy Policy on this page. The date the Privacy Policy was last modified is identified at the top of the page.

Children Under the Age of 13
We do not collect personal information from any person we actually know is under the age of 13 without the consent of the parent or legal guardian of that minor. A parent or guardian may consent to the use of UBC apps by a minor, in which case a parent or guardian is solely responsible for providing supervision of the minor’s use of UBC apps and assumes full responsibility for the interpretation and use of any information or suggestions provided through the apps.

